        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 28 at 6:31PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 631 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over Grant Park-Zoo Atlanta,
or near Atlanta. This storm was nearly stationary.

HAZARD...Up to 40 mph wind, pea sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Atlanta, Decatur, Grant Park-Zoo Atlanta, Candler-Mcafee, Druid
Hills, Midtown, North Druid Hills, Belvedere Park, North Decatur,
West End, Virginia Highland, Sweet Auburn, Turner Field, Piedmont
Park, Kirkwood, Lakewood Park, Panthersville, East Lake, Gresham
Park, and La Vista.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
